^ "Maffei leaving Starbucks' board". The Seattle Times. The Seattle Times. Retrieved 28 April 2017. 
^ "IAC/InterActiveCorp - Current Report". ir.iac.com. Retrieved 2017-04-26. 
^ a b Sisario, Ben. "Live Nation Names Gregory B. Maffei Chairman". New York Times. 
^ "Board of Directors – Zillow Group". www.zillowgroup.com. Retrieved 2017-04-26. 
^ Melby, Caleb. "Malone’s Four Liberty Spinoffs Pay Maffei Combined $57 Million". Bloomberg. 
^ "TripAdvisor - Definitive Proxy Statement". ir.tripadvisor.com. Retrieved 2017-04-26. 
^ "This Weekend’s Barron’s: John Malone May Be Better Than Buffett ~ Best Bets in Asia ~ Broadcom Could Rise 20%". Retrieved 2017-04-26. 
^ "The World's Most Admired Companies for 2017". Fortune. Retrieved 2017-04-19. 
^ "Greg Maffei". www.dartmouth.edu. Retrieved 2017-04-19. 
^ "Donors to the Central Library | The Seattle Public Library". www.spl.org. Retrieved 2017-04-26. 
^ "CEO Greg Maffei giving Liberty a lift" (Business). The Denver Post. March 26, 2010. Retrieved 28 April 2017. 






 
